  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aspiration could induce major respiratory affection. They are often present after stroke. The
      aim of this study is to facilitate swallowing recuperation in stroke patients using
      peripheral laryngeal stimulation and to understand its mechanisms using motor evoked
      potential and cortical evoked potential.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
